 REAL-TIME STOCK MARKET DATA PIPELINE USING PYTHON, APACHE KAFKA, SPARK STREAMING, AND POSTGRESQL

 ABSTRACT

The stock market generates a massive volume of data every second. Traditional batch processing systems are often unable to handle such continuous streams efficiently. This project presents a Real-Time Stock Market Data Pipeline using Python, Apache Kafka, Apache Spark Streaming, PostgreSQL, and Power BI. The system captures stock market data, streams it through Kafka, processes it using Spark Streaming, stores the processed records in PostgreSQL, and visualizes insights through Power BI dashboards.

The proposed solution demonstrates modern data engineering concepts including real-time ingestion, distributed processing, storage, analytics, and visualization. The system is scalable, fault-tolerant, and capable of generating alerts for abnormal stock price movements.

Keywords: Data Engineering, Apache Kafka, Spark Streaming, PostgreSQL, Real-Time Analytics, Stock Market.

CHAPTER 1: INTRODUCTION

 1.1 Background

Financial markets generate large volumes of data continuously. Traders, investors, and analysts require instant access to stock price changes to make informed decisions. Traditional systems process data in batches, causing delays in analysis and decision-making.

1.2 Problem Statement

Many organizations struggle to process stock market data in real time due to limitations in traditional architectures. There is a need for a scalable streaming solution that can collect, process, store, and visualize stock data with minimal latency.

1.3 Objectives

* Collect stock market data continuously.
* Stream data using Apache Kafka.
* Process data in real time using Spark Streaming.
* Store processed records in PostgreSQL.
* Generate alerts for abnormal price fluctuations.
* Visualize insights using Power BI.

 1.4 Scope

The project focuses on building a real-time stock data pipeline capable of handling streaming data and providing meaningful analytics.

